[@Nertea](https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/83952-nertea/)

Something strange is happening on one of the engines.

My mod, KSP\_PartVolumes, gets the size of each part from the  renderer bounds.

For some reason, this part is reporting bounds which are huge:

    // ----------------------------------------------------------------------
    // CryoEngines/Parts/MethaloxEngines/1875/cryoengine-iguanodon-1/cryoengine-iguanodon-1
    // Dimensions: x: 25.98, y: 5.77, z: 25.98
    // Bounding Box Size: 3892503 liters

I'm not sure why, wondering if anything changed recently in the part.  This is apparently the only engine that's showing this issue.

Would you have any idea?
